# Pug Templates

## Structure

```
views/
  layout.pug        ← base layout; all pages extend this
  partials/         ← reusable fragments (nav, footer, pagination)
  mixins/           ← Pug mixins for repeated markup patterns
  *.pug             ← one file per route/page
```

## Extending Layout

```pug
extends layout

block content
  h1 Page Title
```

## Locals

All template locals come from the controller handler's return object — never set locals directly on `res`. Keep template logic minimal; move any real logic to the service.

## Mixins

Prefer mixins in `views/mixins/` over duplicating markup across templates.

## Conventions

- 2-space indent.
- Use `- const` for in-template variables only when unavoidable.
- Link hrefs and form actions must match NestJS route paths exactly.
- Images served from `public/` — reference as `/images/...`.
